    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Scottish hoods that protect the neck and extend to the shoulders, worn from the 18th century, especially for riding; may be attached to an outer garment.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
